cracknuts.config.save.tooltip: Save the configuration from the control panel to the configuration file.
cracknuts.config.dump.tooltip: Dump the configuration from the control panel to a configuration file.
cracknuts.config.load.tooltip: Upload the configuration file to the control panel.
cracknuts.config.write.tooltip.different: The current configuration is not synchronized with the device. Write the configuration from the control panel to the Cracker.
cracknuts.config.write.tooltip: Write the current control panel configuration to the Cracker.
cracknuts.config.read.tooltip: Read the configuration from the Cracker to the control panel.
cracker.name: MODEL
cracker.config.nut.spi.speed.tooltip: Setting the SPI speed will automatically convert the input value to the nearest integer multiple of SCK and calculate the actual rate. This may cause a discrepancy between the input value and the expected value. The data will be sent after pressing Enter.
cracker.config.nut.spi.autoSelect.toolti:
Deselecting this option means that once the SPI is enabled, the chip select signal will be fixed at low and remain active continuously. 
Selecting this option indicates that after the SPI is enabled, the chip select signal will only go low and become active during data transmission.
cracker.config.nut.spi.csnDly.tooltip:
In delay mode, does the chip select signal remain low throughout the delay phase?
Deselecting this option means that during the DELAY, the CS (Chip Select) signal is normally pulled high.
Selecting this option indicates that during the DELAY, the CS signal is fixed at low.
